A Revision to pandas DataFrames - Exercise #3
The pandas library has been imported with its conventional alias, and pandas display options relevant for full result visibility have been set.



Load the data from 'Sales-products-100.csv' into an object called data.

To develop the habit of following best practices, create a copy of data and store it in a new variable named sales_products_data.

Display the top five rows of sales_products_data.




import pandas as pd
pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)
pd.set_option('display.width', 2000)
data=pd.read_csv("Sales-products-100.csv")
sales_products_data=data.copy()
print(sales_products_data.head())


